oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Preconditioned Calves: A Progress Report
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Williams, Donald E.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: preconditioned calves
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The American Association of Bovine Practitioners, in response to the need of the livestock industry, prepared a program in 1968 for certified pre-conditioned calves. The trademark of CPH was registered with the United States patent office. CPH designates that the calves are certified as pre-conditioned for health. This trademark can only be used by those veterinarians participating in the program as outlined by the American Association of Bovine Practitioners.
